1. **Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**

The structure is composed of 12 blocks. It has 5 layers. The blocks are arranged in a somewhat symmetrical, tower-like structure with a square opening near the middle. The blocks vary in shape (rectangular, triangular, cylindrical) and color (red, blue, green, yellow).

| 3 | Rectangular | Green | Horizontal | Middle of the structure |
| 3 | Rectangular | Green | Horizontal | Middle of the structure |
| 5 | Rectangular | Green | Vertical | Supports for the second layer |
| 6 | Rectangular | Yellow | Horizontal | Second layer in the middle |
| 1 | Square | Blue | Vertical | Third layer |
| 13 | Triangular | Red | Vertical | Above the blue block, in the middle |
| 14 | Triangular | Red | Vertical | Above the blue block, in the middle |
| 2 | Square | Blue | Vertical | Above blue block |
| 9 | Rectangular | Yellow | Horizontal | In the opening of the structure |
| 9 | Rectangular | Yellow | Horizontal | In the opening of the structure |
| 13 | Triangular | Red | Vertical | Cap of the structure |
